    <item>
      <title>Poseidon&amp;#039;s Palace? - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/11/14/poseidons-palace/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/11/14/poseidons-palace/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 15 Nov 2025 04:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8473" class="post-8473 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Poseidon&amp;#8217;s Palace?&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, I received my latest house score from the Happy Room Academy (HRA). Thanks to Curt&amp;#8217;s pic, which I added last week, my score is up to 296,900 points.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Filbert asked me if I was collecting shells in order to recreate Poseidon&amp;#8217;s palace!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/filbert-poseidon.jpg" alt="Filbert: Don't tell me... Are you trying to re-create Poseidon's palace?" class="wp-image-8475" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He said it would practically make me royalty. 😛 And he would visit as Prince Filbert, ruler of the sea.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/filbert-ruler.jpg" alt="Filbert: Then I'd visit and pretend to be Prince Filbert, ruler of the sea!" class="wp-image-8474" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I saw a weather bulletin on the bulletin board, reminding me that winter (and snow) will be coming soon. Oof.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/weather-bulletin2025.jpg" alt="-Weather Bulletin- Come November, mornings will start to cool down. We might even see now, so keep warm!" class="wp-image-8476" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Whitney told me that it&amp;#8217;s better to walk for an hour than to run for half an hour. She said she tries to make pleasurable things last as long as possible&amp;#8230;on a pig.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/whitney-pleasurable.jpg" alt="Whitney: I like to make pleasurable things last as long as possible, on a pig!" class="wp-image-8477" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I found Pascal standing near the ocean. He told me that crocodiles can outrun horses on land! I have my doubts about that one, even if crocs can be fast in short bursts.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/pascal-crocodiles.jpg" alt="Pascal: Crocodiles can outrun a horse on land, maaannn. Just think about that." class="wp-image-8478" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;What a croc(k).&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He gave me a ship cannon before plunging into the cold sea.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Truffles asked me how she looked, but there was no option to actually reply. So I was quite surprised when she thought I said she looked like a total movie star! Yeah, I don&amp;#8217;t think so.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/truffles-star.jpg" alt="Truffles: What?! I look like a total movie star? REALLY? DO YOU MEAN IT??" class="wp-image-8479" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Maybe Babe.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Pippy was sick with a cold today, so I gave her some medicine. Get well soon, Pippy!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0ff365ea4b4ae589e18c26b092fe26946a6e14116b63065f41029c8c6138c7c8?s=98&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/11/14/poseidons-palace/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-11-14T23:58:00-05:00"&gt;November 14, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-11-15T00:58:58-05:00"&gt;November 15, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/filbert-poseidon.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>My 5 Most-Wanted Features of ACNH 3.0 - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/11/08/most-wanted-features-3/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/11/08/most-wanted-features-3/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 09 Nov 2025 04:30:32 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-9069" class="post-9069 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;My 5 Most-Wanted Features of ACNH 3.0&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Last week, we learned about the new Version 3.0 update that&amp;#8217;s coming to New Horizons in January. (Need to &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EdRsRyVpF04" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;see the trailer with my thoughts&lt;/a&gt;?) In this entry, I&amp;#8217;m going to rank the features that I&amp;#8217;m most looking forward to. This is just about the (free) Version 3.0 update, not the Switch 2 upgrade. (So, no megaphone listed here.)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Okay, let&amp;#8217;s start the countdown with my 5th most-wanted feature.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;#5: Zelda Items&lt;/h2&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="635" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/top5-zelda.jpg" alt="The Zelda items coming to Animal Crossing: New Horizons 3.0." class="wp-image-9070" sizes="(max-width: 635px) 100vw, 635px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The Legend of Zelda is probably my favorite game series of them all, and I always found it puzzling that New Horizons never had Zelda items. Even the original GameCube game had a Master Sword, and later games added a Triforce, Link&amp;#8217;s outfit, Majora&amp;#8217;s Mask, and more.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The idea of making a Zelda-themed room (or even better, an outdoor forest) sounds so appealing. I&amp;#8217;m sure nearly everyone will be doing the same thing around the same time&amp;#8230;but that&amp;#8217;s okay. I can&amp;#8217;t wait!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;#4: Storing Flowers and Plants&lt;/h2&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/top5-flowers.jpg" alt="Flowers and bushes in storage." class="wp-image-9071" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;For the first year or two of New Horizons&amp;#8217; release, I would sometimes change the flowers on my paths depending on the season. I&amp;#8217;d use orange and black flowers for Halloween, I had some red and white (candy cane colors) around Christmas, and so on. But without the ability to store those flowers, I&amp;#8217;d usually have to sell them. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Of course, some colors (hybrids) can&amp;#8217;t be bought as seeds. So there was no good option if you wanted to regularly cycle through various flowers. It was particularly annoying when you consider flowers could be stored in most previous games. Now it&amp;#8217;ll be easier to save these flowers without sticking them in awkward spots on my island.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;#3: Tourists in Town&lt;/h2&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/top5-tourists.jpg" alt="Tourist: Oh, hello! You live here, right? It's so nice to meet you. I'm Maggie." class="wp-image-9072" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Guests at the new hotel will have decorated, themed rooms to stay in&amp;#8230;but they don&amp;#8217;t have to stay there the whole time. The trailer showed tourists roaming the town, and that just sounds so cool. Seeing fresh faces around your town could really liven things up. Besides, it never seemed realistic the way that campers would just stay in their tent for their entire visit.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Some previous Animal Crossing games let you interact with non-residents, but usually just in the city (City Folk) or on Main Street or the Roost (New Leaf). The GameCube game would occasionally let a former villager return for a visit, but that seemed rare (and they&amp;#8217;re not random visitors). So this is definitely an exciting thing that I&amp;#8217;m looking forward to!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;#2: Resetti&amp;#8217;s Clean-Up Service&lt;/h2&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/top5-resetti.jpg" alt="Should I contact Resetti to reset this area?" class="wp-image-9073" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Sure, multi-crafting will be a time saver&amp;#8230;but nothing like Resetti&amp;#8217;s clean-up service. Redecorating outdoor areas no longer seems like such a huge, tedious chore when Resetti can clear the slate for you in a flash. He can even dispose of flowers for you, or put them in storage! Flowers have a way of breeding out of control in rainy seasons, so this is huge!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;Honorable Mentions&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Before I get to #1, I want to list a few features as honorable mentions. They&amp;#8217;re all cool features, but they didn&amp;#8217;t quite make my top five. Here&amp;#8217;s the list:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;multi-crafting&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;the hotel itself&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;playable video games&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;storage increase to 9,000 items&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Nintendo items&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Splatoon items&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Many of you might be surprised that multi-crafting didn&amp;#8217;t make my top five, and I imagine it would be high on your lists. But at this point (over 5 years into the game), I don&amp;#8217;t do much crafting any more. So it&amp;#8217;s not as helpful to me now as it would have been 4-5 years ago. But I&amp;#8217;ll still use it, especially once I start redesigning some new areas.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;#1: Slumber Islands&lt;/h2&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/top5-slumber.jpg" alt="Which island will you visit? Make a new island." class="wp-image-9074" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Some of you may remember a &lt;a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9IbB31-JY9U" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;video I made in 2019&lt;/a&gt;, about features I&amp;#8217;d like to see in New Horizons. One of the features on my list was a designated play area that we could design, that was completely separate from our town. I wanted to make race courses or obstacle courses without using up a big chunk of the real estate in town.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;At the time, I envisioned it as a barge that we could call over when we wanted to use it. Despite the fact that this new feature is accessed through dreaming (and not on a barge), this is pretty much exactly what I was hoping for!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll be able to make those obstacle courses, starting in January, without taking up half my town. 😛 It&amp;#8217;ll (potentially) let me get more creative and make bigger races than I could before. Of course, I haven&amp;#8217;t played the game online for over a year and I&amp;#8217;ve kinda gotten out of the habit. But I guess I&amp;#8217;ll have to get back into it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Well, that&amp;#8217;s my list. Do you agree with any of my points? Feel free to share your lists in the comments below!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And if you haven&amp;#8217;t yet seen my Tomodachi Life song about the new features coming to New Horizons, please check it out:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="New Horizons 3.0 Summarized in a Tomodachi Life Song (Animal Crossing ACNH)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/juBfWAlBGSM?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;h2 class="wp-block-heading"&gt;This Week in Forest&lt;/h2&gt;    &lt;p&gt;In other news, life goes on in Forest. This wasn&amp;#8217;t a particularly eventful week on my island, but here are some highlights:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Monday night, I returned Wisp&amp;#8217;s spirits to him. He rewarded me with a pop-up toaster.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped Gullivarrr on Wednesday, and he sent me another pirate-ship cannon in the mail.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Thursday, I sold 8 bugs (7 wasps and a scorpion) to Flick for 38,250 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Yesterday, I returned a lost item to Agent S. She thanked me with an argyle sweater.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Tonight, K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;Surfin&amp;#8217; K.K.&amp;#8221; for me. No other villagers attended the show.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;See you all next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/11/08/most-wanted-features-3/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-11-08T23:30:32-05:00"&gt;November 8, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-11-08T23:45:10-05:00"&gt;November 8, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/top5-zelda.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>HRA Score: Zero - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/11/08/hra-score-zero/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/11/08/hra-score-zero/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 09 Nov 2025 00:43:16 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8461" class="post-8461 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;HRA Score: Zero&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, Curt wanted to have a competition to see who could catch a crucian carp&amp;#8230;with legs! I don&amp;#8217;t think anyone is going to find one of those with legs! 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/curt-carplegs.jpg" alt="Curt: Who can catch a crucian carp first, with legs?!" class="wp-image-8462" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday must have been Dharma Day, because Nookington&amp;#8217;s had both the regular and mini-dharmas!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/2dharmas.jpg" alt="Timmy: Ah, yes, yes. That's the mini-dharma. Very nice. ...very nice." class="wp-image-8463" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Filbert was complaining about his latest Happy Room Academy evaluation. Apparently, his score was literally zero! Wow! You can&amp;#8217;t get any worse than that!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/filbert-0.jpg" alt="Filbert: ...my room's a mess! I can't believe that coordination earned me 0 points." class="wp-image-8464" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Whitney was talking about La-Di-Day, and she wished that it ran longer than just one day. She wanted to sing until dawn, on a pig.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/whitney-dawn2.jpg" alt="Whitney: They should at least let me sing until dawn, on a pig!" class="wp-image-8465" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As for La-Di-Day, today was the day. Truffles said that once her song is chosen as the town tune, talent scouts won&amp;#8217;t stop calling her.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/truffles-scouts.jpg" alt="Truffles: The talent scouts will swarm this town and won't stop calling me!" class="wp-image-8466" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She said it&amp;#8217;s hard being a chart-topping pop star. Wow.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/truffles-popstar.jpg" alt="Truffles: Sometimes it's hard being a chart-topping pop star, you know." class="wp-image-8467" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I wouldn&amp;#8217;t know. And neither would you.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Since my town tune isn&amp;#8217;t that old anyway, I didn&amp;#8217;t ask anyone to sing me any new options this time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When I went to visit Filbert, I saw that his house was completely empty! And all of a sudden, his HRA score of zero suddenly made sense.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/filbert-empty.jpg" alt="Filbert's completely empty house." class="wp-image-8468" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He was planning on moving out of town, and villagers will usually pack up their furniture in boxes. But apparently, he didn&amp;#8217;t have any furniture! The last time I visited him, he only had some fish and some clothes on display. I knew fish and bugs wouldn&amp;#8217;t be packed up, but the same must apply to clothes as well. At any rate, I talked him out of moving.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As I walked near the river, Curt surprised me by giving me his picture!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/curt-picture.jpg" alt="Curt: Here... This is, uh, my picture, with legs. Here's hoping you like it." class="wp-image-8469" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I took it home and put it on display in my Gulliver room. His favorite quote is on the back: &amp;#8220;I&amp;#8217;m watching you!&amp;#8221; 👀&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/curt-pic.jpg" alt="Curt's pic on display in my house." class="wp-image-8470" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0ff365ea4b4ae589e18c26b092fe26946a6e14116b63065f41029c8c6138c7c8?s=98&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/11/08/hra-score-zero/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-11-08T19:43:16-05:00"&gt;November 8, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/curt-carplegs.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Riverside Bike Ride - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/11/07/riverside-bike-ride/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/11/07/riverside-bike-ride/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 08 Nov 2025 03:27:38 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13694" class="post-13694 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Riverside Bike Ride&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Now that November is here, mushrooms can be found around town. That also includes a piece of mush furniture each day, which will be disguised as a mushroom (like this mush bed).&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8395-sm.jpg" alt="Jeff, holding up a mushroom: WHOA!" class="wp-image-13695" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Big Top told me he was planning on moving out of town, but I told him to stay. However, that didn&amp;#8217;t convince him. So I kept speaking to him to try to change his mind, and he wondered if I kept talking to him just because I liked his cologne.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8396-sm.jpg" alt="Big Top: Is it because you like my new coleslaw cologne, J-boo?" class="wp-image-13696" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Way too many of my villagers have started using Big Top&amp;#8217;s catchphrase, &amp;#8220;in a coma.&amp;#8221; So when Deena asked for a new one, I jumped at the chance. I told her to say &amp;#8220;I&amp;#8217;m down&amp;#8221; instead. Of course, it&amp;#8217;s a pun on the down feathers that ducks have.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8397-sm.jpg" alt="Deena: Let's see... I'm down!" class="wp-image-13697" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As I continued talking to Big Top throughout my session, he started talking about his desire to ride a bike alongside the river! I don&amp;#8217;t think a bike exists that would support the weight of an elephant, but it&amp;#8217;s a nice idea at least.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8398-sm.jpg" alt="Big Top: On days like today, riding a bike by the river sounds pretty sweet!" class="wp-image-13698" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rosie asked me to play a game of hide-and-seek, and I agreed to the competition. She gave me 15 minutes to find her, Fang, and Big Top. Within a minute, I found Big Top trying to hide behind Nook &amp;#8216;n&amp;#8217; Go.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8399-sm.jpg" alt="Big Top hides behind Nook 'n' Go during a game of hide and seek." class="wp-image-13699" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;A few minutes later, I found Rosie behind the museum and Fang behind this sign board. So none of them actually hid behind a tree this time, surprisingly. And I found all of them within five minutes!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8400-sm.jpg" alt="Fang hides behind a sign board during a game of hide and seek in Animal Crossing: City Folk (ACCF) for Nintendo Wii." class="wp-image-13700" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rosie was frustrated to lose the game so quickly.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8401-sm.jpg" alt="Rosie: Grrr! I can't believe you found me so fast! It's so totally frustrating!" class="wp-image-13701" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But she rewarded me with a tall nebuloid for winning the game.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over by the museum, I shot down a balloon present that contained a koopa shell. Now I can relax and just kick it.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full is-resized"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8402-sm.jpg" alt="A balloon present flies near the museum." class="wp-image-13703" style="width:500px;height:auto" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;A bit later, Rosie noticed a walkingstick sticking out of my pocket!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8403-sm.jpg" alt="Rosie: Did I really just see a walkingstick sticking out of your pocket...?" class="wp-image-13704" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She offered to give me a harp for it, and that sounded like a great deal (with no strings attached). 🎶&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Even though I talked to Big Top many, many times, he never brought up moving again. So either he changed his mind about moving without explicitly mentioning it, or he&amp;#8217;s still planning on moving and just didn&amp;#8217;t bring it up again for some reason. But I had the game on for nearly two hours (though I wasn&amp;#8217;t playing continuously), so I gave it up for the night. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maybe I&amp;#8217;ll give it a quick try again tomorrow or Sunday, but there&amp;#8217;s a chance he might move. I&amp;#8217;d hate for his stay to end this way, but I didn&amp;#8217;t want to spend all night working on it either. Hopefully he&amp;#8217;ll be okay. See you all next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/11/07/riverside-bike-ride/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-11-07T22:27:38-05:00"&gt;November 7, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/RUU_8395-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Halloween, Mush Season - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/11/01/halloween-mush-season/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/11/01/halloween-mush-season/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 02 Nov 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-9056" class="post-9056 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Halloween, Mush Season&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday, I returned a lost item to Ankha. It was her purse!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ankha-purse-sm.jpg" alt="Ankha: Oh! How wonderful! My purse! I've been looking everywhere for this!" class="wp-image-9058" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Losing a purse is a big deal&amp;#8230;so you&amp;#8217;d think she&amp;#8217;d give a really nice reward for returning, right? Well&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ankha-box-sm.jpg" alt="Ankha: I'm sorry to give you more to carry... but for helping me, you should have a cardboard box." class="wp-image-9059" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Just a cardboard box. And there&amp;#8217;s nothing in the box. 😉 Oh well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Flora the pink ostrich (who resembles a flamingo) was camping at the campsite. I like her, but I did not ask her to move in.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/flora-camper-sm.jpg" alt="Flora, at the campsite: Hi there! I'm Flora, and I'm totes camping on your awesome island!" class="wp-image-9060" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday was Halloween, and I met up with Jack outside of Resident Services.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/halloween2025-sm.jpg" alt="Jack: This is a night for frights and delights, which comes but once a year--that's right! Halloween is here!" class="wp-image-9061" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I changed into my skeleton costume, and I began giving candy to villagers for spooky items.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/peanut-spooky-sm.jpg" alt="Peanut: Now here's a treat for YOU! Have a spooky wall!" class="wp-image-9063" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I also did some trick-or-treating to score more candy. 🍬&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/bones-hween-sm.jpg" alt="Bones: Now, let's Halloween the heck out of tonight, at the Depot!" class="wp-image-9062" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After giving candy to a few villagers, I got a couple lollipops in return. Jack gave me a spooky carriage for one of them, and I consider that to be the &amp;#8220;grand prize&amp;#8221; of Halloween. But I also got Jack&amp;#8217;s robe and Jack&amp;#8217;s face, so I dressed up as the Czar of Halloween to trick my villagers. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/static-hween2025-sm.jpg" alt="Static: J-J-Jack! Please don't trick me! Please! Here, take some candy!" class="wp-image-9064" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/peanut-apprentice-sm.jpg" alt="Peanut: Has the time finally come? Are you here to steal me away...and turn me into your apprentice? I'm SO ready." class="wp-image-9065" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Shortly after that, I wrapped up my game for the night. I went on to spend more time in the &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/10/31/spooky-coincidence/"&gt;City Folk&lt;/a&gt; version of Halloween.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tonight, I ran into Pascal while doing some diving. He said that maybe once in a while, we actually &lt;em&gt;should &lt;/em&gt;put the cart before the horse.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/pascal-cart-sm.jpg" alt="Pascal: Maybe we should put the cart before the horse sometimes. I bet horses like to mix things up once in a while." class="wp-image-9066" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He gave me a pearl in exchange for the scallop I caught.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I attended K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s show at the plaza. He performed &amp;#8220;Spring Blossoms&amp;#8221; for me, Bob, and June. Not exactly the most seasonal song, but it was still good.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="600" height="357" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/kk-11125.jpg" alt="K.K. Slider performs for Jeff (dressed as Jack), Bob, and June." class="wp-image-9057" sizes="auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And now that November is here, mushrooms can be found on the ground again.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/elegant2025-sm.jpg" alt="Jeff, dressed as Jack, admires an elegant mushroom." class="wp-image-9067" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As you&amp;#8217;ve probably heard, Nintendo announced that Version 3.0 of Animal Crossing: New Horizons is coming out in January! If you&amp;#8217;d like to view the trailer, with my thoughts in text across the top, check this out:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="My Thoughts on the Animal Crossing New Horizons 3.0 Trailer (and Switch 2 version)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/EdRsRyVpF04?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;What are you all looking forward to most in Version 3.0? Let me know in the comments, and I&amp;#8217;ll see you next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/11/01/halloween-mush-season/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-11-01T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;November 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-11-02T00:48:28-04:00"&gt;November 2, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/ankha-purse-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
